definitions.definition: Of or pertaining to the male gender ; manly .
Of or pertaining to the male sex ; biologically male, not female.
Belonging to males; typically used by males.
Having the qualities stereotypically associated with men : virile , aggressive , not effeminate .
Of, pertaining or belonging to the male grammatical gender , in languages that have gender distinctions.

subdefinitions.definition: Being of the masculine class or grammatical gender, and inflected in that manner.
examples: The noun Student is masculine in German.

subdefinitions.definition: Being inflected in agreement with a masculine noun.
examples: German uses the masculine form of the definite article, der , with Student .

definitions.definition: Having the vowel harmony of a back vowel .
definitions.label_groups: grammar , Mongolic languages , of any word

definitions.definition: Following or ending on a stressed syllable.
examples: Masculine caesura , masculine catalexis , masculine ending , masculine rhyme .
